What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Insecticide Seed Treatment Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Insecticide Seed Treatment Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the insecticide seed treatment market will project a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 11.30% during the forecast period of 2021-2028. Increasing advancements in the crop science techniques, surge in the demand for products that help to maintain crop health, and rapidly increasing industry competitiveness are attributable to the growth of insecticide seed treatment market. This means that the insecticide seed treatment market value, which was USD 2.7 billion in 2020, will climb up to USD 6.36 billion by the year 2028.

From the name itself, it is clear that insecticide seed treatments are the chemicals that are used for the purpose of protection from insects, pathogens, and other pests. Not just that, the insecticide seed treatment chemicals are also used to maintain the health and quality of the seeds.

Rising costs of high quality seeds will emerge as the major factor fostering the growth of insecticide seed treatment market. Rising focus on the innovative crop protection methods will also act as an important factor determining the growth of market. Increased focus on the technological advancements in integrated pest management systems coupled with rising use of insecticides as a low-cost crop protection solution will further create lucrative and remunerative growth opportunities for the market. Rising industrialization, globalization and increased personal disposable income will also carve the way for the growth of the market.

However, fluctuations in the prices of raw materials and risk factor associated with the use of chemicals will pose a major challenge to the growth of insecticide seed treatment market. Also, rising environmental concerns will further slow down the insecticide seed treatment market growth rate.

